(Edited after major updates.) This is a fantastic app, with clearer pictures than my stock camera app (Nexus 5). There are some functions that you didn't know you needed until you discovered them (e.g. Object removal, Group shot, Time lapse). The non-standard menu is a bit tricky until you have become used to it. HDR gives outstanding results, albeit at the cost of being significantly slower, whereas Single-shot DRO mode yields great results fast. Depending on lighting and speed requirements, you need to swap between HDR and DRO for the best images; you also need to experiment with their settings to get the best results for your hardware. The video also gives truer colours than my stock app. Panorama unfortunately is buggy, distorted, and far beneath the standard of the latest Nexus 5 updates. This app lacks Photosphere. Apart from Panorama and Photosphere, this is my camera app of choice, well worth the price. Please add Photosphere and fix Panorama, and I'll have no need to use the Nexus 5's stock app.
